      • generateGCode

        public String generateGCode()
        End matrix (the pose of the robot arm gripper) is stored on the PC in the text format "G0 X.. Y.. Z.. I.. J.. K.. T..\n" where XYZ are translation values and IJK are euler rotations of the matrix.
        Returns:
        the text format for the current pose.

      • parseGCode

        public void parseGCode(String line)
        End matrix (the pose of the robot arm gripper) is stored on the PC in the text format "G0 X.. Y.. Z.. I.. J.. K.. T..\n" where XYZ are translation values and IJK are euler rotations of the matrix. The text, if parsed ok, will set the current end matrix of the ghost.
        Parameters:
        line - the text format of one pose.

      • approximateJacobian

        public double[][] approximateJacobian(DHRobot robot,
                                      DHKeyframe keyframe)
        Use Forward Kinematics to approximate the Jacobian matrix for Sixi. See also https://robotacademy.net.au/masterclass/velocity-kinematics-in-3d/?lesson=346

      • inDirectDriveMode

        protected boolean inDirectDriveMode()
        Direct Drive Mode means that we're not playing animation of any kind. That means no gcode running, no scrubbing on a timeline, or any other kind of external control.
        Returns:
        true if we're in direct drive mode.
